string is the collection of the characters surrounded by single quotes, double quotes, or triple quotes. 
strings can be created by enclosing the character or the sequence of characters in the quotes.
Python allows us to use single quotes, double quotes, or triple quotes to create the string.


#Cannot we use single quotes inside single quotes?
"""
#characteristics of strings:
a='never 'loss your self' confidence'
print(a)

#o/p= invalid syntax
because cant give like this syntax
"""


#Cannot we use double quotes inside double quotes
"""
b="never "loss your self" confidence"
print(b)
#o/p= invalid syntax
"""

#we can use double quotes inside single quotes
"""
c="never 'loss your'confidence"
print(c)
#o/p=never 'loss your'confidence
"""

#we can single quotes inside the double quotes
d='never "loss your" confidence'
print(d)
#o/p=never loss your confidence




"""
#multiline string:
a=""hii friends
how are you""
print(a)
"""


